 NOLLYWOOD actress, Ayo Ade-Kosh has stated that she won’t feature in a porn film even if offered billions of Naira. In a recent interview with The Nation, the actress and producer says no amount of fund in the world would tempt her to accept such a role. “There is no amount of money that can tempt me to do such, not in this lifetime or any other lifetime.” The University of Lagos graduate of Psychology also stressed that she sticks to movie roles that don’t challenge or pose challenges to her marriage. “My husband is comfortable with me being an actress and I stick to roles that won’t disrespect my marriage,” she stressed. The actress, who became popular for her role in Yoruba movie, ‘Asiri’ says she has never had to play a role that will cause her embarrassment.